text:
It's more like a 3.5 star rating. It was decent food. Nothing to brag about. The good things about this place are; 
1. The pulled pork had a nice flavor 2. They actually have sweet tea already made, and it's pretty good. 3. Big Red, whaaaaa?!? I haven't found that in the north ever. Only seen it in the south. 4. The jalapeño sausage was the best part of this meal. 

Now the bad;
1. I LOVE brisket and that's why I came.... this brisket didn't tickle my tummy the way delicious brisket does. 
2. The mac-n-cheese was not good at all.
